      <h1 class='title'>Co-ordinated On-line Register of Electors</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 19 May 2004 vol 421 cc52-3WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_52ws' title='Col. 52WS &mdash; HC Deb 19 May 2004 vol 421 c52WS' name='column_52ws' href='#column_52ws' rel='bookmark'>52WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0421P2_20040519_CWS_5'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-nick-raynsford' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0421P2_20040519_CWS_5' title='Link to this speech by Mr Nick Raynsford' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-nick-raynsford" title="Mr Nick Raynsford">The Minister for Local and Regional Government (Mr. Nick Raynsford)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Today, I am pleased to announce to the House the launch of a consultation on modernising electoral registration. This follows on from my written statement on the 15 January 2004,<span class="italic">Official Report,</span> columns 42&#x2013;43WS, when I announced the launch of the coordinated online register of electors (CORE) project. At that time I gave a commitment to consult with local government and others on the details for taking forward the project, including the proposed funding arrangements.</p><p>This project will contribute to the modernisation of the electoral registration process in Great Britain by, first, standardising local electoral registers and, secondly, allowing authorised users to access local registration data centrally. It will support the achievement of our aim to hold a multi-channelled e-enabled general election sometime after 2006</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_53ws' title='Col. 53WS &mdash; HC Deb 19 May 2004 vol 421 c53WS' name='column_53ws' href='#column_53ws' rel='bookmark'>53WS</a><p>Stakeholders will have until 13 August 2004 to send in their responses.</p><p>Copies of the consultation document are available in the Libraries of both Houses and will also be made available on the website of the Office of the Deputy Prime Minister.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
